                            <comment id="13708036" author="xieliang007" created="Sun, 14 Jul 2013 14:14:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the compaction trigger condition will be inaccurate sometimes. e.g. set minFilesToCompact=3, it probably trigger a minor compaction while storefiles.size() - filesCompacting.size() = 2. or storefiles.size() - filesCompacting.size() = 4, but didn&apos;t trigger a normal minor compaction request.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13715803" author="lhofhansl" created="Mon, 22 Jul 2013 22:53:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Why would this be a 0.94 issue only? I see the same synchronization missing in trunk (it just more complicated in trunk because of the compaction policies).&lt;br/&gt;
Also, it seems there are other places were we miss synchronization: exploringCompactionSelection, completeCompaction, compactionSelection, &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
